description.text: Definition of the Submodel Extension IEC 81346 of HierarchicalStructures identified by its semanticId. The Submodel idShort can be picked freely.
Base entry point for the Entity tree in this Submodel, this must be a Self-managed Entity reflecting the Assets administrated in the AAS this Submodel is part of. Inherits from EntryNode

Base entry point for the Entity tree in this Submodel, this must be a Self-managed Entity reflecting the Assets administrated in the Asset Administration Shell this Submodel is part of. The idShort of the EntryNode can be picked freely and may reflect a name of the asset.
The Entity AspectNode can be a co-managed or self-managed entity representing an Aspect.

Used to classify objects based on code letters across three levels. The first letter represents the class (example: B), the two letters represent the sub-class (example: BA), the three letters represent the sub-sub-class (example: BAB) based on the applicable standard.
Used to classify objects based on code letters across three levels. The two letters represent the sub-class (example: BA) based on the applicable standard.
Used to classify objects based on code letters across three levels. The third level represents the sub-sub-class (example: BAB) based on the applicable standard.
Serves to further refine the classes, if the same letter codes are assigned in a system, the number is incremented in each case. (e.g.: BAB1, BAB2, ...). This achieves uniqueness in a system.
Brief description of the aspect in question. The description should be self-explanatory, as it also serves to define the ‘OtherAspect’.
PrefixLevel for the precise differentiation of an aspect and its characteristics. The appropriate AspectNode must be selected based on this prefix.
HierarchyPrefix to define the representation of the reference designator.
Modeling of logical connections between components and sub-components. Either this or "IsPartOf" must be used, not both.

Can be a Co-managed or Self-managed entity. A Node reflects an element in the hierarchical model is set into relation with one or more defined relations. The name of a node can be picked freely but it must be unique in its hierarchical (sub-)level.
Constraint SM_IEC81346_001: Only allowed to point to a ProductAspectNode.

Constraint SM_IEC81346_002: Only allowed to point to a LocationAspectNode.
Constraint SM_IEC81346_003: Only allowed to point to a FunctionAspectNode.
